markets.title: Will **NYC** average less than 1,500 new COVID-19 cases per day by March?
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for New York City is below 1,500 for a single day between Issuance and March 01, 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occured, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for March 01, 2022, or 10:00 AM on March 08, 2022.

markets.title: Will **NYC hit a new peak COVID-19 case average** by January 31?
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for New York City is above 40,465 for a single day between Issuance and January 31, 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occurred, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for January 31, 2022, or 10:00 AM on February 09, 2022.

markets.title: Will **New York City** average more than 30,000 new COVID-19 cases per day by the end of the year?
markets.subtitle: >30K
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for New York City is above 30,000 for a single day between Issuance and December 31, 2021, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occured, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for December 31, 2021, or 10:00 AM on January 07, 2022.
